HEADWORD: Ostension
<hw>Os*ten"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ostensio</ets> a showing: cf. F. <ets>ostension</ets>. See
<er>Ostend</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The showing of the
sacrament on the altar in order that it may receive the adoration of the
communicants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ostensive</ent>⟦br⟧
